It will finish its work in March and then dissolve, because this experiment must have a definite time limit.
In June, the mayor announced, "we will present the strategic plan, using the work done by the Commission for the future of Roma Capitale".
He said that the Commission was useless because its opinions would not be binding. Alemanno replied: 'Everything depends on the work the Commission is able to do and the quality of its proposals.
If quality is there, as in France with the Attali Commission and as I am sure in Rome too, its contribution will be fundamental.
